1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:03,400
I’ll hold
accountable each of those who separated us.

2
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:06,839
Whoever shares Haydar’s blood...

3
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:09,240
will taste death from my hand.

4
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:14,040
I live to take revenge
on those who did this to me.

5
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:16,760
The opportunity came to
drown Ateş in his own blood.

6
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:19,520
I’ll make Mercan regret running
from me too.

7
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:21,656
He escaped from the hospital.

8
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:23,200
He couldn’t have escaped without help.

9
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:25,280
Could Nezir be involved in this?

10
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:26,560
I don’t know.

11
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,280
But I wouldn’t be surprised if it was him.

12
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,200
There’s no need for Mercan to get hurt.

13
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:34,320
You didn’t use to say that before, Haydar.

14
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:36,920
What makes you think you can point a gun at
me, Haydar?

15
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:39,856
If you try to do business trusting
those jackals you used to work with,

16
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:43,000
they’ll sell you out to Ateş for pennies.

17
00:00:43,360 --> 00:00:44,800
You had Haydar stabbed, didn’t you?

18
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:47,640
Yes. I did.

19
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:50,080
I’m loyal to the oath I made.

20
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,720
If you had stayed
calm, Haydar would be in prison right now.

21
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:57,680
He escaped my hands this time, that
bastard, but I’ll chase him until he dies.

22
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,440
I hear you’ve
been searching for me everywhere.

23
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:02,760
You
started a war you’re going to lose, Haydar.

24
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,640
You should have killed me when you had the
chance, Ateş.

25
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:11,920
If you have any sense, both you and Haydar
will turn yourselves in.

26
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,160
No one can send me back to that prison.

27
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:16,680
No one!

28
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,120
Enjoy your life, Ateş.

29
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,960
Because the countdown has started.

30
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:27,280
You've been on this journey with
Ates and Mercan from the very beginning.

31
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:30,600
Every twist, every
heartbreak. Every moment.

32
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:33,439
And now we reach the end.

33
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:35,359
This isn't something to watch alone.

34
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,679
This is something we experience together.

35
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:43,240
Episodes 98, 99 and 100 will not
be available on any memberships.

36
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:46,800
They will premiere
on YouTube for all of us at the same time.

37
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,319
One moment.

38
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:51,199
One story. One ending.

39
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,759
So grab your comfy blanket and a
huge bucket

40
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,760
of popcorn for one final twist.

41
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,840
Let's be there together.

42
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:47,040
Death is very close to you, Ateş. Very!

43
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:50,760
Dad!

44
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,000
Dad, how could you do this?

45
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:02,440
And you, why did you escape
from prison? Didn’t you think of us at all?

46
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,320
Answer me!

47
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:09,640
Stay
out of this, Mercan. You’ve gone too far.

48
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:14,280
I’m already involved. You’re talking about
hurting the people I love.

49
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:20,320
And you, how could you cooperate with
Nezir? Haven’t you heard what he did to me?

50
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:27,200
Mercan, my love, won’t you even greet me?

51
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,400
Shut the hell up! Shut up!

52
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:46,560
Dad, please surrender.
If you serve your sentence...

53
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:50,360
maybe, maybe we’ll have a chance. Please.

54
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:58,920
Dad!

55
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:31,120
What’s wrong, Haydar? Getting emotional?

56
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:35,320
If only it were possible to go back...

57
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,680
Did hearing
Mercan’s voice make you back down, Haydar?

58
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,320
If Ateş hadn’t entered our lives...

59
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:48,640
Are you going to cry?

60
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,240
Look at mighty Haydar Yıldırım!

61
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,160
Gone all soft.

62
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,200
Those were the days!

63
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,040
You’ll even forgive Ateş now.

64
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:18,279
Listen to me, don’t you dare
do such a thing. If you change your mind...

65
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:19,280
Stop talking nonsense!

66
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:27,920
Nothing has
changed. It’s exactly as we said.

67
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,760
When did my father escape?

68
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,880
Recently.

69
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,920
You knew. Why didn’t you tell me, Ateş?

70
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:56,520
I’m around. If you need anything, just say
the word.

71
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,240
Why didn’t you tell me my father escaped?

72
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,280
I found out on my birthday.

73
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:11,080
We were having a good day.

74
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:13,480
You didn’t tell me so I wouldn’t get upset.

75
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:19,400
I can’t believe this. How is this possible?
How did he escape?

76
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:27,920
He must have gotten help from Nezir.

77
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:33,400
Why? Why, Ateş? Why are
they doing this to us?

78
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:39,360
Their goal is clear. But they won’t reach
it.

79
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:45,040
This won’t ever end, will it? Will all this
evil never stop?

80
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:53,840
It will. Haydar stole my past.

81
00:06:56,800 --> 00:07:02,760
He won’t steal my future,
our future. He will never separate us.

82
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:07,760
Never. They won’t separate us.

83
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,080
Our plan is working perfectly.

84
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,640
We lit the first fuse.

85
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:13,160
Aren’t you comfortable? Want me
to bring you something to drink?

86
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,000
No.

87
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:24,080
No need. I’m exactly as I should be.

88
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:29,800
These are beautiful days, you know.

89
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:34,800
I will punish Ateş with my own hands.

90
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:41,640
Then what
are we waiting for? Let’s finish this man.

91
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,600
No. That won’t do.

92
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:51,440
Slowly. Savoring every moment.

93
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,560
Listen to me.

94
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:02,400
I have no patience left.
Ateş took everything from me.

95
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,800
Whatever we’re going
to do, let’s do it soon.

96
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,360
If I said we’ll wait, we’ll wait.

97
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:20,120
My life has passed waiting.

98
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:28,960
We saw the
lover’s roads, but forget it, let’s eat.

99
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,560
Let’s lose ourselves.

100
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,560
God forbid.

101
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,360
This guy has completely lost it.

102
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,520
Ms. Ayşe.

103
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:18,800
Don’t turn your back on Malik.

104
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,280
You’re mother and son.
Flesh and blood cannot be separated.

105
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:28,680
No matter what, even if you
fight or fall out, you can’t break apart.

106
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:31,720
Malik is angry, but it will pass.

107
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:37,159
Don’t leave Malik and
go. He’ll be very upset.

108
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:39,280
Why are you doing this?

109
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,760
You know I don’t want you.

110
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:52,360
I did everything to stop you from marrying
my son.

111
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,040
You know that.

112
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,000
Why are you being kind to me?

113
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,920
Because there’s no other way.

114
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,000
You are my elder.

115
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,840
You are
Malik’s mother. The woman who raised him.

116
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:15,120
That is enough for me to respect you.

117
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:28,360
I can’t believe all this. Cemal just told
me.

118
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:31,400
What are we going through?

119
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:35,200
I don’t know, Demet. I don’t know what to
do.

120
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:39,440
The
only thing I know is we must stay standing.

121
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:46,920
While my father threatens
the man I love, I can’t just sit and watch.

122
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,560
Maybe you should postpone the wedding?

123
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:58,440
I mean, maybe you’d feel more at ease.

124
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:02,440
I’m scared too, Mercan.

125
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:08,680
No, Demet. We’ve
postponed our happiness enough for others.

126
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,080
I
Won’t let anyone stand in our way anymore.

127
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:25,560
Still, I think we should be cautious.

128
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:34,560
Anyway, I have things to do. I should go.

129
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Mercan.

130
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:51,880
Maybe Demet is right.
Should we postpone the wedding?

131
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:54,119
I’ve been thinking about that too for a few
days.

132
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:58,840
No. Postponing the wedding
means giving them what they want.

133
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:01,480
We won’t do that.

134
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:06,640
We would only postpone it. After things
calm down, we’d still have the wedding.

135
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:10,680
Besides, you didn’t want
a wedding. What changed?

136
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:17,520
Now I do. You were right
when you said they can’t steal our future.

137
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:22,360
We shouldn’t let them take our happiest day
from us.

138
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:30,840
That day is
the 187th day. It’s very meaningful for us.

139
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:37,080
The day we thought everything
would end, we’ll make brand new beginnings.

140
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,480
You were the one
who got me into all this wedding business.

141
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:47,280
Now you’re trying to talk me out
of it. Don’t you see something off here?

142
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:53,480
When have I ever gone back
on a promise I made to you, Ms. Mercan?

143
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,120
That’s how a good husband should be.

144
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:06,680
What are you?

145
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,560
What am I like?

146
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:18,720
Different.

147
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:23,920
Different from everyone.

148
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:26,520
Unique.

149
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:37,200
Your courage fascinates me, and I like that
a lot.

150
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,920
Life taught me not to be afraid.

151
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,799
I mean, I do get scared...

152
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:53,840
I just realized my fears make me stronger.

153
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:59,120
That you shouldn’t surrender, you
should stand your ground.

154
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,520
My fearless princess.

155
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,320
Still, be careful.

156
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,200
Don’t go out alone.

157
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:14,720
Or
I’ll have to lock you in your room again.

158
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,480
Yes, sir.

159
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,160
Yes, Yaşar?

160
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:33,160
Okay, I was going
to check it on the computer anyway.

161
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,520
I already sent an email.

162
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:41,280
Wait a second.

163
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,280
I need to go upstairs.

164
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:44,320
Okay.

165
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,000
I’ll come and check.

166
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,800
Yes, officer.

167
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,200
I’m listening.

168
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:09,600
Zehra, with all this henna night
and wedding, we’ll be overwhelmed.

169
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:11,640
We should check the pantry today.

170
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:18,840
Mom, how
will we manage all this when you’re gone?

171
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,760
You do everything so well.

172
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:23,680
The soup is done too.

173
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,640
Let’s taste it, how is it?

174
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:30,680
Come here.

175
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,280
Mom, something smelled strange to me.

176
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:38,560
What smelled?

177
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:44,600
It smells great. Just look.

178
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,760
No, mom, thanks.

179
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,920
Oh come on. What’s wrong with it?

180
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:56,520
Look, you felt nauseous earlier too.

181
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,680
Zehra, could you really be pregnant?

182
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,440
Oh mom.

183
00:17:04,120 --> 00:17:05,839
Don’t get excited for nothing.

184
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:07,680
I must have just caught
a chill in my stomach.

185
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,040
Alright then.

186
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,560
Go see a doctor.

187
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,560
And get a blood test while you’re there.

188
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:16,960
Or wait.

189
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:19,200
Let’s call Berat, he
can go to the pharmacy.

190
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,800
You know those tests with two lines?

191
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,840
We’ll
check and wait to see if it’s one or two.

192
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,400
Mom, don’t involve Berat now.

193
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,160
I’m telling you, it’s nothing. I’d know
if it was.

194
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:32,880
No, you might not know.

195
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:34,199
Sometimes it happens like that.

196
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:37,200
My experience is speaking. Trust me.

197
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:38,960
Let’s go buy those tests.

198
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:42,160
We’ll wait excitedly like in the shows.

199
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,600
Was it one line or two? Which was it?

200
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:48,640
Mom, let’s just finish our work.

201
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,440
Here, take the test.

202
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,800
Let’s have Berat get it.

203
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:53,320
Oh, a grandchild is coming.

204
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:54,840
Wait, let me see, I’ll know.

205
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:01,520
I swear there’s a baby, Zehra, I’m telling
you.

206
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:02,480
I know these things.

207
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:04,159
Oh my God.

208
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:07,760
God, please
accept my prayers, a grandchild is coming.

209
00:18:08,120 --> 00:18:09,480
I’ll love that baby so much.

210
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:11,880
Oh, oh, oh.

211
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:15,320
Thank God, hopefully.

212
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,840
Should he get the test?

213
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:20,920
Let’s call Berat.

214
00:18:20,921 --> 00:18:24,240
Mom, wait, let’s finish our work.

215
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,720
Okay, okay, let’s finish.

216
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,200
Let me check again.

217
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,760
Alright, thanks.

218
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,080
The police checked everywhere possible.

219
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:47,520
There’s still no trace.

220
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:52,560
They know Haydar and Nezir are together.

221
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,360
If we catch one, we’ve got the other.

222
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:01,600
They
realized they couldn’t do anything alone.

223
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:05,999
They think they’ll fire
their final shot together.

224
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,760
God is my witness, I’ll
see them taken down, mark my words.

225
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,480
Cemal.

226
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:19,240
Don’t let Mercan know
about the developments.

227
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:21,680
She
shouldn’t get stressed before the wedding.

228
00:19:23,080 --> 00:19:24,360
You’re right.

229
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:26,080
I know.

230
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:27,880
She won’t stay calm, I know.

231
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,360
But we’ll manage.

232
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:32,840
This needs to end as soon as possible.

233
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,280
I’m tired of even seeing those men...

234
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:42,240
I don’t even have the strength to tolerate
them breathing anymore.

235
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:45,520
Even the breaths they take are a sin.

236
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,480
Then again, they’re not even men.

237
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,960
One
day they’ll fall into the pit they deserve.

238
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:02,640
I’ll cover them up and close this chapter.

239
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,400
Alright.

240
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:16,320
I sent this too.

241
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:18,560
That’s done as well.

242
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,680
Enjoy your life, Ateş.

243
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,080
Because the countdown has started.

244
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,680
Death is very close to you, Ateş.

245
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,280
Very.

246
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:42,840
I won’t let them ruin our happiness.

247
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,760
I won’t let them smile.

248
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:50,440
They won’t get what they want.

249
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,200
Can you move aside?

250
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,480
I won’t.

251
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,080
What’s that in your hand?

252
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,000
I had the photos framed.

253
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,080
Don’t change the subject.

254
00:21:28,081 --> 00:21:29,440
They look great.

255
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,040
They really look great.

256
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:33,920
But you already saw my suit.

257
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:36,200
It’s not the same.

258
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,400
The groom can’t see the wedding dress.

259
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,520
Where should we hang this?

260
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:41,960
Why not?

261
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:47,176
Because you have to wait until the wedding
day, Mr. Groom.

262
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,200
Sorry.

263
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,440
Come here.

264
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,960
It’ll look nice here.
This is the best spot.

265
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:00,520
I waited a lifetime for you without knowing
you.

266
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:02,760
I can wait a little more
knowingly, no problem.

267
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,320
It looks great.

268
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:32,120
This time the dress is white, right?

269
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:35,760
Not black like last time, I hope.

270
00:22:36,360 --> 00:22:38,120
Though that was beautiful too.

271
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,000
Who knows.

272
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:41,480
Be open to surprises.

273
00:22:41,481 --> 00:22:45,440
You’ll have
to wait until the wedding day to find out.

274
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,720
Until then, don’t make me mad.

275
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,280
Or I might run away from the wedding.

276
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:51,080
That will never happen.

277
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:53,880
Wherever you go...

278
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,480
Roads, distances, people...

279
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,560
Nothing can stop me.

280
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:00,640
Sure, sure.

281
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,760
You’d find me even with your eyes closed.

282
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,400
Of course I would.

283
00:23:04,480 --> 00:23:05,480
Go on, tie it.

284
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,800
You must be joking.

285
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,359
No, I’m serious.

286
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:11,640
Tie my eyes.

287
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:14,520
Come on.

288
00:23:15,680 --> 00:23:16,680
Tie them.

289
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:45,080
Wherever you run, I’ll find you.

290
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,640
By your scent.

291
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:29,279
Even
if you go to the other side of the world...

292
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,720
I’ll find you.

293
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,640
We are not two separate people anymore.

294
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:38,360
We are one.

295
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:48,399
So even if we’re apart...

296
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,120
We’re destined to reunite.

297
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,200
I had checked on Mercan.

298
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:16,080
I had some work downstairs too.

299
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:54,240
I took care of it.

300
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:01,520
Well...

301
00:26:01,521 --> 00:26:03,479
I got hungry...

302
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,560
I came to get something.

303
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:07,839
I thought food would be...

304
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:08,760
In the kitchen.

305
00:26:08,761 --> 00:26:11,199
Of course, food would be...

306
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:13,040
In the kitchen, where else?

307
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:15,439
And I’m sure Ms. Binnaz...

308
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,040
Prepared wonderful things.

309
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,720
Enjoy your meal.

310
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:37,080
Want me to prepare something for you too?

311
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:39,240
We can eat here together.

312
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:43,600
Sure.

313
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:03,360
Do you really like it?

314
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:07,680
I do. I like it a lot.

315
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:11,000
You’ll look like a fairy at the wedding.

316
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:17,600
At least my mistake led to something good.

317
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,160
Look, you found love.

318
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:23,600
Ateş...

319
00:27:23,601 --> 00:27:24,760
Ateş is a good man.

320
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,880
What’s wrong, Mom? Why are you crying?

321
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:33,000
I don’t know, my dear.

322
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:36,136
I guess
I’ve become more emotional as I got older.

323
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:39,360
I cry at everything now.

324
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:46,160
I remembered the day you first married
Ateş.

325
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,440
I was so selfish toward you.

326
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,760
It hurts when I think about it.

327
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:03,400
What we did to you was very cruel.

328
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:07,760
I made many mistakes, Mercan. Many.

329
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:16,080
Now the
only thing I want is for you to forgive me.

330
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:19,240
Please forgive me.

331
00:28:25,680 --> 00:28:28,280
Mom, everyone makes mistakes.

332
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:30,520
I already forgave you.

333
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:33,720
I won’t make you regret it.

334
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:36,760
I’ll make up
for everything I left incomplete.

335
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:42,360
I’ll file for divorce from your father.

336
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:51,800
Mom, I need to tell you something.

337
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,120
What is it, dear?

338
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:01,280
My father...

339
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:02,880
My father escaped from prison.

340
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:08,520
What? How? Are you sure, Mercan?

341
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:10,640
He threatened Ateş on the phone.

342
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:12,920
So he escaped.

343
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,800
How could he do this?

344
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:19,680
I’ll call him now and make him explain what
escaping means.

345
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:22,920
You can’t
call him, Mom. He doesn’t have his phone.

346
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:25,880
I must have lost my mind.

347
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:28,400
You said he called and all...

348
00:29:29,320 --> 00:29:33,000
But
you’ll see, he’ll find a way to call me.

349
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:35,440
Then he’ll see what I’m capable of.

350
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,320
Don’t be
afraid, dear. He can’t do anything to you.

351
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:45,040
I’m not afraid.

352
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,120
What he’s done is more than enough.

353
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:50,480
From now on, I’m here with you.

354
00:29:52,320 --> 00:29:57,000
How was I so blind, so careless?

355
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,640
You’ve been driving me crazy since morning,
Haydar.

356
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:43,720
Sit down here.

357
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:48,120
I don’t take orders from you.

358
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:51,240
You will take orders from me.

359
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:54,040
Why did you kidnap Mercan?

360
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,640
Why do you think I did?

361
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:02,120
Out of love, devotion,
my attachment to her, maybe?

362
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:05,000
You didn’t hurt her, did you?

363
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,000
Drop the concerned father act.

364
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:09,680
You’re dealing with Nezir. I’m not buying
it.

365
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:11,840
Oh Mercan, Mercan.

366
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:16,640
You kidnapped her, and what did it change?

367
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:20,600
You couldn’t defeat either Mercan or Ateş.

368
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:27,280
Listen.

369
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:30,080
If you don’t want a hole in your head, shut
up.

370
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:37,080
If your daughter had
behaved, we’d be touring Europe right now.

371
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:38,840
What did she do?

372
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:42,760
Ateş, Ateş, Ateş, nonstop.

373
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:44,720
But wait.

374
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:46,360
She’ll be mine eventually.

375
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:49,080
Then I’ll settle that score with him.

376
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,560
Then let’s finish this guy today.

377
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:54,440
You take
Mercan, everyone goes their own way.

378
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:55,600
Come on.

379
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:57,560
Drop it.

380
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:58,720
Stop talking nonsense.

381
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:02,960
Before we find Ateş, he’ll find us.

382
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,520
You’re boring, Haydar.

383
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:16,000
Were you always like this,
or did you become this way later?

384
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:21,640
Ateş’s fate is in my hands.

385
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:23,840
And the countdown has started.

386
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:26,880
Tick.

387
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,200
Tock.

388
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:29,440
Tick.

389
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,600
Tock.

390
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:31,920
Tick.

391
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,200
Tock.

392
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:34,760
Tock.

393
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:38,120
Tock.

394
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:40,400
Tick.

395
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:16,840
I found you too.

396
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:20,480
You did.

397
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,320
I stopped by the garden kitchen.

398
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:24,440
They had just taken them out of the oven.

399
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,320
They’re very good.

400
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:35,160
Really very good.

401
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:37,000
I was starving.

402
00:33:38,720 --> 00:33:39,720
What were you doing here?

403
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:43,840
Ms. Zahide sent the
plans for the mall construction.

404
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:45,480
I was looking at them.

405
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:52,320
I can’t focus on anything these days.

406
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:56,480
Does your mother know?

407
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,400
I told her just now.

408
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:07,680
She’ll file for divorce from my father.

409
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:10,120
She also apologized to me.

410
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:27,960
So what happened?

411
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:33,200
This is partly from happiness too.

412
00:34:35,200 --> 00:34:38,240
I’m feeling a mother’s affection for the
first time.

413
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:45,960
I realized something in
me was always missing.

414
00:34:48,680 --> 00:34:50,960
A
Mother’s affection is something beautiful.

415
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:57,840
It is.

416
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:21,680
So you cry and eat at the same time?

417
00:35:24,360 --> 00:35:25,760
It’s from stress.

418
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:31,440
Let me call the event company.

419
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:33,880
They asked me to choose the flowers. I’ll
handle that.

420
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:39,520
Didn’t you bring me those pastries?

421
00:35:40,120 --> 00:35:41,120
Where?

422
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,520
Should I put some more?

423
00:36:16,160 --> 00:36:19,200
No, this is already too much for me.

424
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:22,216
But Ms. Binnaz
did an amazing job again. It’s delicious.

425
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:24,360
Yes, Binnaz outdid herself again.

426
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:27,400
My mother used to make this dish well too.

427
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:31,480
She would add plenty of tomatoes.

428
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:39,800
I’ve been thinking about them a lot lately.

429
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:51,200
I wonder if things would
be like this if they were alive.

430
00:36:58,440 --> 00:36:59,440
May they rest in peace.

431
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:03,400
Amen.

432
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,680
My father was a difficult man.

433
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,240
But my mother was like an angel.

434
00:37:18,640 --> 00:37:21,560
It’s been about nine years. Since
then, it’s just been me and my brother.

435
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:30,480
When I lost my mother, I was very scared.

436
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:38,560
I thought, what if
I lose my brother too, what if I’m alone?

437
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:44,800
And now I am alone.

438
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:48,520
Demet, don’t cry.

439
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:52,760
Sorry.

440
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,160
This isn’t something
to apologize for, Demet.

441
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:02,600
I only said it so you wouldn’t be upset.

442
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,639
And look, you’re not alone.

443
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,520
Mercan is here.

444
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:11,240
I’m here.

445
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:22,400
We’re here, Ateş is here.

446
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:25,520
That’s what I meant.

447
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:32,560
We know very well what
it means to be alone.

448
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:37,640
How did you lose your family?

449
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:45,160
I never had a family, Demet.

450
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:50,760
I must have been three
or four when I was left at the orphanage.

451
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,600
They found me on the street.

452
00:38:54,640 --> 00:38:56,120
And no one ever claimed me.

453
00:39:01,320 --> 00:39:02,320
I’m sorry.

454
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:05,440
I didn’t mean to bring it up.

455
00:39:07,440 --> 00:39:08,600
You don’t need to feel sorry.

456
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:15,040
It’s not something you bring up or forget
anyway.

457
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:22,360
No matter what you do…

458
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:24,360
Wherever you are in life…

459
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:27,280
It finds a way to remind you.

460
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:32,480
Didn’t you ever wonder?

461
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,560
Didn’t you ever want to find them?

462
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:39,920
Of course I wondered, Demet.

463
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:43,200
I wondered a lot.

464
00:39:48,600 --> 00:39:52,600
We searched everywhere. Ateş
and I turned the world upside down.

465
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,680
But nothing came of it.

466
00:39:57,920 --> 00:40:03,080
Did they lose me, or did they abandon me?

467
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:06,280
What kind of people were they?

468
00:40:07,120 --> 00:40:09,280
Are they alive or dead? I know nothing.

469
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:19,120
Anyway, I think I talked too much.

470
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:22,200
Thanks for the food.

471
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:42,480
He managed to escape from there.

472
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:51,400
Honestly, that
man is scary. You never know what he’ll do.

473
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:57,080
Alright, mom, calm down. Don’t worry.

474
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:00,560
We’ll be careful.

475
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:03,920
He doesn’t really have
an issue with us anyway.

476
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:07,480
Hopefully
he gets caught soon without harming anyone.

477
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:10,440
Mr. Ateş and
the others are already after him.

478
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:15,320
Either the police
or our people will find him soon.

479
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:16,840
Of course.

480
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:24,080
Whoever is bad always loses right when they
think they’ve won.

481
00:41:25,080 --> 00:41:29,400
Hopefully he’ll stumble soon.

482
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:32,160
Hopefully.

483
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:35,120
Don’t worry, mom.

484
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:38,200
Ateş and the
others are after him. The police too.

485
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:39,880
Relax. He’ll be caught.

486
00:41:47,160 --> 00:41:51,120
Ms. Ayşe, welcome. Please come in.

487
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:54,920
Make some space, dear.
Please, come this way.

488
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:58,400
Welcome.

489
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,360
Welcome.

490
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:03,760
Welcome.

491
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:06,960
Dear, pour some tea for Ms. Ayşe.

492
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:16,200
No, thank you. I didn’t come for tea.

493
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,760
I came to apologize.

494
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:51,640
This time I truly am sorry. I thought I was
right, but I was wrong.

495
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:04,920
I won’t come between you anymore.

496
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:10,920
Forgive me.

497
00:43:22,360 --> 00:43:25,240
What is this? A new game?

498
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:27,200
Malik.

499
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:31,320
I wish I could believe you, mom.

500
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:34,760
But after everything, it’s very hard.

501
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:49,960
I can’t tell what’s true or false anymore.

502
00:43:51,960 --> 00:43:52,960
I don’t know.

503
00:43:55,080 --> 00:43:56,080
You’re right.

504
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:02,960
If
I were you, I wouldn’t believe me either.

505
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:11,520
But you’re a part of me.

506
00:44:13,680 --> 00:44:14,920
Forgive me.

507
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:51,800
Someone must know something.

508
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:56,320
Fine. Do whatever it takes, find out.

509
00:44:58,120 --> 00:44:59,120
Alright.

510
00:45:00,720 --> 00:45:01,720
No trace at all?

511
00:45:04,320 --> 00:45:05,679
I feel trapped everywhere.

512
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:09,040
Hang on,
brother, we’ll find him. I just got a call.

513
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:11,120
They found one of Haydar’s old men.

514
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:13,400
News will come any moment.

515
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:18,440
By the way, you said to
increase security at the mansion.

516
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:19,640
I handled it like you said.

517
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:27,400
If only
we could find him… anything from the phone?

518
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:31,480
I don’t think much will come out
of it, don’t get your hopes up.

519
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:35,600
You’re tired too. Take
some time for yourself.

520
00:45:37,440 --> 00:45:40,600
Don’t be ridiculous.
I’ve had issues with time for a while now.

521
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:45,600
Issues with time.

522
00:45:47,320 --> 00:45:48,320
With Demet?

523
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:51,280
What do you mean, Demet?

524
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:52,720
Yes, Demet.

525
00:45:54,160 --> 00:45:56,520
We run into each other sometimes.

526
00:45:56,800 --> 00:45:58,560
We talk when we do, naturally.

527
00:45:59,080 --> 00:46:01,399
We talked a bit in the kitchen earlier.

528
00:46:01,400 --> 00:46:04,360
She asked
if I wanted something to eat, that’s all.

529
00:46:05,360 --> 00:46:07,400
When someone gets caught in something this
strong…

530
00:46:09,400 --> 00:46:10,640
At first, they can’t accept it.

531
00:46:15,200 --> 00:46:16,200
Remember?

532
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:21,560
I resisted a lot about Mercan too.

533
00:46:23,320 --> 00:46:24,840
Before I understood my feelings…

534
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:28,080
Before I could even admit them to myself…

535
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:30,800
You had already figured most of it out.

536
00:46:31,880 --> 00:46:35,800
What does that have to
do with this now? Come on.

537
00:46:43,320 --> 00:46:44,320
What is it like?

538
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:48,800
Ask your heart. It knows.

539
00:46:50,200 --> 00:46:51,960
It will guide you the right way.

540
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:57,080
Me, with Nezir’s sister? No way.

541
00:46:57,960 --> 00:47:00,999
You told me once…

542
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:02,720
Not to fight your feelings.

543
00:47:05,240 --> 00:47:06,560
Don’t fight either.

544
00:47:08,840 --> 00:47:11,680
You won’t win that fight.

545
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:14,040
Love destroys everything in its path.

546
00:47:16,320 --> 00:47:17,800
It doesn’t listen to Nezir or anyone.

547
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:23,040
Phone… they’re calling.

548
00:47:25,280 --> 00:47:26,280
Hello?

549
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:30,160
Alright. Don’t let
him slip away. Bring him here immediately.

550
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:32,616
They caught the man. They’re bringing him.

551
00:47:32,640 --> 00:47:33,640
Move.

552
00:47:35,640 --> 00:47:37,000
Alright then.

553
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:38,800
As agreed.

554
00:47:40,360 --> 00:47:42,000
Okay. Thank you. We’ll be in touch.

555
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:46,840
Thanks, dear.

556
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:48,280
Enjoy your meal.

557
00:47:49,280 --> 00:47:50,280
How’s it going?

558
00:47:51,520 --> 00:47:54,840
I handled the flower arrangements
too. Everything is falling into place.

559
00:47:58,480 --> 00:48:00,600
Happiness suits you well.

560
00:48:02,200 --> 00:48:03,400
It suits you too.

561
00:48:04,400 --> 00:48:05,480
I saw you.

562
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:07,640
You were in the kitchen with Cemal.

563
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:10,480
You should’ve come.

564
00:48:11,000 --> 00:48:13,560
No, I was going to go to Ateş anyway.

565
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,120
I didn’t want to disturb you.

566
00:48:16,120 --> 00:48:18,280
Disturb what, Mercan?

567
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:20,360
I don’t know.

568
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:23,280
Come on now.

569
00:48:23,720 --> 00:48:26,360
That’s what I’m saying, let it be.

570
00:48:27,280 --> 00:48:28,760
No, it’s nothing like that.

571
00:48:30,760 --> 00:48:34,999
Even if I wanted something else…

572
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:36,520
It wouldn’t be right, Mercan.

573
00:48:38,120 --> 00:48:39,999
After everything that happened…

574
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:44,679
Thinking about what my brother did…

575
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:45,680
No.

576
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:50,280
Cemal and I are just friends.

577
00:48:51,440 --> 00:48:52,440
This is better.

578
00:48:53,480 --> 00:48:55,760
He didn’t imply anything either.

579
00:48:56,760 --> 00:48:59,800
It’s impossible.

580
00:49:02,840 --> 00:49:03,960
But at first…

581
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:06,880
You used to say maybe about Ateş…

582
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:08,960
Now I understand you better.

583
00:49:12,520 --> 00:49:14,119
My dear friend…

584
00:49:14,120 --> 00:49:15,999
No matter what I said…

585
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:17,040
I couldn’t escape love.

586
00:49:19,240 --> 00:49:21,640
I only delayed the inevitable a little.

587
00:49:23,040 --> 00:49:24,119
Don’t do that.

588
00:49:24,120 --> 00:49:25,200
Don’t delay it.

589
00:49:27,880 --> 00:49:30,760
But ours isn’t like yours…

590
00:49:31,320 --> 00:49:32,880
Don’t postpone your happiness.

591
00:49:34,440 --> 00:49:36,600
Yes, we were born into the wrong families.

592
00:49:37,320 --> 00:49:38,960
But we loved the right men.

593
00:49:40,120 --> 00:49:42,120
When life gives you such a gift…

594
00:49:43,920 --> 00:49:45,280
You shouldn’t miss it.

595
00:50:03,520 --> 00:50:04,520
Haydar.

596
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:07,600
Believe me, my guys cook really well.

597
00:50:08,600 --> 00:50:09,600
Look at this.

598
00:50:10,880 --> 00:50:13,440
They made it perfectly.

599
00:50:19,680 --> 00:50:20,680
What’s wrong?

600
00:50:22,760 --> 00:50:25,320
You’re too quiet, that’s not like you.

601
00:50:29,640 --> 00:50:30,760
Something happened to you.

602
00:50:38,760 --> 00:50:39,760
Anyway.

603
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:43,720
I ate too much.

604
00:50:44,400 --> 00:50:47,480
Guys, bring me some tea.

605
00:50:58,920 --> 00:50:59,920
Come on.

606
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:04,840
Here you go, boss.

607
00:51:12,480 --> 00:51:13,480
What’s this?

608
00:51:14,120 --> 00:51:15,120
Tea, boss.

609
00:51:17,760 --> 00:51:23,600
How many times have I told you to bring it
in a glass, not a paper cup?

610
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:26,920
Take this away.

611
00:51:35,400 --> 00:51:36,760
What am I supposed to do now?

612
00:51:37,400 --> 00:51:40,640
I’ve said it fifty
times, I drink tea from a glass, not paper.

613
00:51:44,160 --> 00:51:45,920
They don’t understand me.

614
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:51,320
What are you looking at?

615
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:56,840
Were you always this crazy?

616
00:51:57,840 --> 00:51:59,480
Or did you lose your mind later?

617
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:01,680
I’ve never seen you like this.

618
00:52:02,800 --> 00:52:05,680
Have you ever seen an oak tree grow from an
apple seed, Haydar?

619
00:52:07,040 --> 00:52:08,040
You are what you are.

620
00:52:10,240 --> 00:52:12,760
And you know this better than anyone.

621
00:52:16,160 --> 00:52:17,280
What’s wrong with me anyway?

622
00:52:18,400 --> 00:52:19,440
I’m a fine man.

623
00:52:21,720 --> 00:52:22,760
What do you mean?

624
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:26,640
Poor Murat…

625
00:52:27,520 --> 00:52:29,600
He always wanted to be bad like you.

626
00:52:32,560 --> 00:52:36,120
Ms. Müzeyyen competes with you in cruelty.

627
00:52:39,520 --> 00:52:41,000
Looks like he takes after his mother.

628
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:44,120
How do you know that?

629
00:52:45,320 --> 00:52:47,160
I know everything, Haydar.

630
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:49,040
I know everything.

631
00:53:02,400 --> 00:53:03,400
No.

632
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:05,880
No, you can’t work with this lunatic.

633
00:53:06,680 --> 00:53:08,120
He’s completely lost his mind.

634
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:21,600
Handle your own business, Mr. Haydar.

635
00:53:50,200 --> 00:53:51,200
Where is he?

636
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:53,480
Where
is Haydar with that lowlife boss of yours?

637
00:54:04,880 --> 00:54:05,880
Where is Nezir?

638
00:54:07,840 --> 00:54:10,240
I don’t know. He hasn’t been around for a
while.

639
00:54:15,440 --> 00:54:16,560
Think again.

640
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:19,800
Brother, I swear I don’t know.

641
00:54:20,080 --> 00:54:21,520
Don’t swear, you’ll get struck down.

642
00:54:23,200 --> 00:54:25,520
I swear on my children,
I don’t know, brother.

643
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:28,200
Don’t drag your
kids into this, you heartless man.

644
00:54:29,760 --> 00:54:33,120
I’m giving you
one day. Maybe you’ll come to your senses.

645
00:54:34,800 --> 00:54:36,600
If he catches me, he’ll kill me anyway.

646
00:54:40,600 --> 00:54:41,520
Even better.

647
00:54:41,521 --> 00:54:44,400
Tell me where he is, I’ll protect you.

648
00:54:44,720 --> 00:54:46,000
He won’t be able to do anything.

649
00:54:46,360 --> 00:54:48,040
I don’t know, I swear I don’t.

650
00:54:52,320 --> 00:54:53,720
Lock him up somewhere.

651
00:54:54,800 --> 00:54:56,040
Maybe he’ll come to his senses.

652
00:54:57,000 --> 00:54:58,000
Get up. Move.

653
00:54:58,760 --> 00:54:59,760
Move.

654
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:10,160
I believe your mother is sincere, Malik.

655
00:55:11,400 --> 00:55:16,240
After everything we’ve been through,
I can’t be as trusting as you, my love.

656
00:55:17,720 --> 00:55:19,880
But if you don’t forgive her, we can’t be
fully happy.

657
00:55:20,720 --> 00:55:21,960
Give her another chance.

658
00:55:22,920 --> 00:55:24,080
For my sake.

659
00:55:26,320 --> 00:55:28,480
What are we going
to do with your good intentions?

660
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:31,560
We’ll use them for good things.

661
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:51,880
Malik.

662
00:55:53,640 --> 00:55:56,280
Son, come on, kiss your mother’s hand.

663
00:56:01,320 --> 00:56:05,359
There’s no such thing
as holding grudges within a family.

664
00:56:05,360 --> 00:56:07,320
Even enemies forgive each other.

665
00:56:08,440 --> 00:56:10,160
Don’t upset your mother anymore.

666
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:11,800
Come on, kiss her hand.

667
00:56:21,560 --> 00:56:22,880
Malik is right.

668
00:56:29,560 --> 00:56:35,240
She saw that love for
the first time in you.

669
00:56:39,960 --> 00:56:41,720
And I tried to ruin it.

670
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:59,080
I should have done
this much earlier, but… fate… it’s now.

671
00:57:16,280 --> 00:57:19,640
This is a family heirloom.

672
00:57:22,160 --> 00:57:24,520
It was passed down to me from my mother.

673
00:57:36,120 --> 00:57:39,560
And from me to my beautiful daughter.

674
00:58:06,760 --> 00:58:07,760
Come.

675
00:58:18,840 --> 00:58:19,920
Come.

676
00:59:03,560 --> 00:59:05,520
We got a lot done today, didn’t we?

677
00:59:10,520 --> 00:59:11,520
Ateş.

678
00:59:12,400 --> 00:59:13,480
What’s wrong? Are you okay?

679
00:59:14,800 --> 00:59:17,136
Don’t worry. It’s not my blood,
it must have gotten on me from somewhere.

680
00:59:17,160 --> 00:59:19,360
What happened again?

681
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:22,760
Mercan, you’re asking
too many questions again.

682
00:59:23,320 --> 00:59:26,320
This blood is about my
father or Nezir, right?

683
00:59:27,640 --> 00:59:29,440
Is there news?

684
00:59:30,000 --> 00:59:31,000
Don’t worry.

685
00:59:32,680 --> 00:59:33,680
I’ll catch them soon…

686
00:59:34,840 --> 00:59:36,280
and hand them over to justice.

687
00:59:37,400 --> 00:59:38,920
I’m worried about you.

688
00:59:42,000 --> 00:59:43,440
They both hold a grudge against you.

689
00:59:44,800 --> 00:59:46,040
They’re both very dangerous.

690
00:59:46,920 --> 00:59:48,720
With a guardian angel like you by my side…

691
00:59:51,280 --> 00:59:54,079
nothing will happen to me.

692
00:59:54,080 --> 00:59:55,880
Don’t think about these things now.

693
00:59:56,800 --> 00:59:58,680
Think about our wedding.

694
00:59:59,120 --> 01:00:00,280
And of course, our honeymoon.

695
01:00:01,120 --> 01:00:03,280
I’ll go check the study, I have
a few tasks to handle.

696
01:00:08,120 --> 01:00:13,760
Hello, Ms. Zahide?

697
01:00:37,960 --> 01:00:39,440
Where is Haydar?

698
01:01:07,640 --> 01:01:08,640
Where the hell is Haydar?

699
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:15,160
Where is he, where is Haydar?

700
01:01:18,400 --> 01:01:19,800
He escaped, brother.

701
01:01:20,800 --> 01:01:21,800
He took a gun.

702
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:47,760
Good. Let’s finish him today.

703
01:01:51,600 --> 01:01:54,080
You take Mercan however you want, everyone
goes their own way.

704
01:01:54,200 --> 01:01:56,760
No one, no one can ruin my plan.

705
01:02:00,360 --> 01:02:04,080
Not Ateş, not Haydar, not idiots like you.

706
01:02:04,960 --> 01:02:08,040
Understood?

707
01:02:08,920 --> 01:02:09,920
Damn it!

708
01:02:14,800 --> 01:02:15,800
No one can ruin my plan.

709
01:02:18,040 --> 01:02:19,040
You’re here?

710
01:02:26,600 --> 01:02:30,440
I just finished my work too.

711
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:21,976
I need to send an email to Ms. Zahide now.

712
01:03:22,000 --> 01:03:24,336
Alright, you handle
your work, I’ll walk in the garden a bit.

713
01:03:24,360 --> 01:03:26,800
Come join me
in the gazebo when you’re done.

714
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:31,200
It won’t take long anyway.

715
01:03:31,680 --> 01:03:33,320
Okay, you take care of it.

716
01:03:33,920 --> 01:03:35,360
Dad!

717
01:03:35,960 --> 01:03:38,200
Mercan!

718
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:33,000
Mercan!

719
01:04:35,200 --> 01:04:36,200
Ateş!

720
01:04:37,320 --> 01:04:38,320
Shut up, be quiet!

721
01:04:40,120 --> 01:04:41,120
Don’t you dare, Mercan!

722
01:04:42,320 --> 01:04:43,480
Don’t!

723
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:46,200
Kes sesini kes!

724
01:04:52,560 --> 01:04:53,560
Sakın Mercan!

725
01:04:54,520 --> 01:04:55,520
Sakın!

726
01:05:30,720 --> 01:05:31,720
Don’t!

727
01:05:46,640 --> 01:05:47,640
You...

728
01:05:48,000 --> 01:05:49,320
What are you doing here?

729
01:05:50,280 --> 01:05:52,120
I
Have unfinished business with your husband.

730
01:05:52,560 --> 01:05:53,679
I came to see him.

731
01:05:53,680 --> 01:05:55,720
I won’t let you harm Ateş.

732
01:05:56,120 --> 01:05:58,320
Go turn yourself
in. Sooner or later, you’ll be caught.

733
01:05:59,360 --> 01:06:01,200
You disappointed me, Mercan.

734
01:06:01,480 --> 01:06:03,560
No, you’re the one who disappointed us!

735
01:06:04,080 --> 01:06:05,680
With what you’ve done, your threats...

736
01:06:06,320 --> 01:06:08,080
Look at yourself.

737
01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:10,056
You’re pointing a gun at your own daughter.

738
01:06:10,080 --> 01:06:11,920
Everything I did, I did for you.

739
01:06:12,400 --> 01:06:14,120
I didn’t want you to go through what I did.

740
01:06:14,480 --> 01:06:16,280
You’ve never known hunger.

741
01:06:16,520 --> 01:06:17,880
You’ve never lived on the streets.

742
01:06:18,200 --> 01:06:18,840
Don’t!

743
01:06:18,841 --> 01:06:21,279
Don’t you dare
use us as an excuse for your evil, don’t!

744
01:06:21,280 --> 01:06:24,560
Whatever
you did, you did for yourself, understand?

745
01:06:29,680 --> 01:06:30,680
Ungrateful!

746
01:06:53,960 --> 01:06:55,159
You...

747
01:06:55,160 --> 01:06:57,160
I don’t recognize you anymore.

748
01:06:59,760 --> 01:07:01,199
You’ve joined forces with that man.

749
01:07:01,200 --> 01:07:04,480
Ateş or Tahir, whatever
his name is, I’ll kill him tonight.

750
01:07:06,320 --> 01:07:08,560
I’ll take his life, and you won’t stop me,
Mercan.

751
01:07:09,600 --> 01:07:10,720
He took everything from me.

752
01:07:11,840 --> 01:07:13,880
I have nothing left to lose.

753
01:07:26,280 --> 01:07:30,000
Ms. Zahide, I’ve just
sent you an email. Is there anything else?

754
01:07:32,760 --> 01:07:33,760
Alright.

755
01:07:34,320 --> 01:07:36,680
I’ll set the meeting time and message you.

756
01:07:38,680 --> 01:07:39,760
Okay, talk soon.

757
01:08:06,800 --> 01:08:07,800
Dad!

758
01:08:07,960 --> 01:08:08,960
Dad, turn yourself in.

759
01:08:09,480 --> 01:08:10,880
I’m telling you, turn yourself in.

760
01:08:11,280 --> 01:08:12,800
I won’t have peace until Ateş is dead.

761
01:08:13,360 --> 01:08:15,400
He’ll pay for what he did with his life.

762
01:08:15,840 --> 01:08:16,840
Do you understand?

763
01:08:17,160 --> 01:08:19,600
And I’m telling you, I won’t let you harm
him.

764
01:08:20,120 --> 01:08:22,360
If you want
to kill him, you’ll have to kill me first.

765
01:08:23,840 --> 01:08:24,840
Mercan!

766
01:08:40,920 --> 01:08:41,920
Mercan!

767
01:08:46,480 --> 01:08:47,880
Ateş!

768
01:08:54,720 --> 01:08:55,720
Let go!

769
01:08:57,480 --> 01:08:58,680
Don’t come any closer!

770
01:08:59,920 --> 01:09:00,920
Let go! Let go, Mercan!

771
01:09:01,240 --> 01:09:01,880
Mercan!

772
01:09:02,120 --> 01:09:03,120
I said let go!

773
01:09:03,200 --> 01:09:04,200
Let go!

774
01:09:16,640 --> 01:09:17,640
Mercan!

775
01:09:19,360 --> 01:09:20,360
Haydar!

776
01:09:21,560 --> 01:09:22,560
Ateş!

777
01:09:23,040 --> 01:09:24,040
Mercan!

778
01:09:24,240 --> 01:09:26,800
Mercan, are you okay? Are you hurt?

779
01:09:27,280 --> 01:09:28,360
I’m fine. Are you okay?

780
01:09:28,880 --> 01:09:29,880
I’m fine.

781
01:09:30,960 --> 01:09:31,960
Are you okay?

782
01:09:32,840 --> 01:09:33,840
I’m fine.

783
01:09:34,560 --> 01:09:35,560
Don’t worry.

784
01:09:44,640 --> 01:09:45,680
Are you asleep?

785
01:09:46,800 --> 01:09:48,440
Haydar got right under your nose.

786
01:09:49,040 --> 01:09:50,040
Go after him.

787
01:09:50,520 --> 01:09:52,760
Run, run, run!

788
01:09:55,800 --> 01:09:56,800
What’s happening?

789
01:09:57,080 --> 01:09:58,720
What was that sound?

790
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:04,440
What’s going on?

791
01:10:14,040 --> 01:10:15,040
Burak!

792
01:10:15,880 --> 01:10:17,080
Take Mercan too.

793
01:10:17,200 --> 01:10:18,800
Take everyone inside the mansion.

794
01:10:19,240 --> 01:10:22,360
Don’t step
outside until you hear from me, understood?

795
01:10:22,520 --> 01:10:24,880
Berat, tell Binnaz not to leave the house.

796
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:25,960
Run, run!

797
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:27,879
You all get inside too, quickly!

798
01:10:27,880 --> 01:10:29,440
Come on, hurry, let’s go.

799
01:10:29,480 --> 01:10:30,480
Come on, girl. Come on.

800
01:10:30,640 --> 01:10:32,560
Ateş, please don’t go.

801
01:10:34,400 --> 01:10:36,560
Don’t worry, nothing will happen to me.

802
01:10:37,080 --> 01:10:38,760
I won’t leave you alone, I promise.

803
01:10:39,400 --> 01:10:40,400
Come on.

804
01:10:40,520 --> 01:10:41,600
We’re going.

805
01:10:42,320 --> 01:10:42,600
Come on. Mercan.

806
01:10:43,120 --> 01:10:43,680
Mercan, come on.

807
01:10:43,880 --> 01:10:45,160
Come on, girl, let’s go.

808
01:10:45,240 --> 01:10:46,240
Come on. Mercan.

809
01:10:46,840 --> 01:10:47,840
Ms. Müzeyyen.

810
01:10:48,080 --> 01:10:49,000
Are you okay?

811
01:10:49,080 --> 01:10:50,080
Aslı, come on.

812
01:10:50,280 --> 01:10:51,280
Ateş.

813
01:10:58,480 --> 01:10:59,760
Mother, go inside.

814
01:11:00,120 --> 01:11:01,120
Inside, inside, inside.

815
01:11:01,240 --> 01:11:02,360
What happened?

816
01:11:04,160 --> 01:11:05,680
Mr. Haydar came to shoot Mr. Ateş.

817
01:11:07,240 --> 01:11:08,240
What?

818
01:11:08,680 --> 01:11:09,000
Yes.

819
01:11:09,320 --> 01:11:10,360
Son, what are you saying?

820
01:11:10,960 --> 01:11:12,199
What misfortune has befallen me!

821
01:11:12,200 --> 01:11:13,000
Come on inside, mother.

822
01:11:13,040 --> 01:11:15,120
Son, don’t go, Berat, please don’t go.

823
01:11:15,240 --> 01:11:16,600
Mother, go inside, come on.

824
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:18,440
Did anything happen to Mr. Ateş?

825
01:11:18,800 --> 01:11:20,119
Everyone’s fine, mother, everyone.

826
01:11:20,120 --> 01:11:21,000
Mr. Ateş is fine, everyone’s fine.

827
01:11:21,040 --> 01:11:22,040
Go inside.

828
01:11:22,680 --> 01:11:24,360
How did that man get in there?

829
01:11:24,400 --> 01:11:25,800
God forbid.

830
01:11:25,880 --> 01:11:26,960
Be careful, alright?

831
01:11:27,040 --> 01:11:28,776
Alright,
don’t worry. I’ll go check and come back.

832
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:29,640
Be careful, brother.

833
01:11:29,641 --> 01:11:31,120
Okay, don’t worry.

834
01:11:35,560 --> 01:11:37,280
Mercan, drink this.

835
01:11:38,160 --> 01:11:39,160
Thanks.

836
01:11:44,360 --> 01:11:45,360
Give it to me.

837
01:11:54,040 --> 01:11:55,040
Are you okay, dear?

838
01:12:03,960 --> 01:12:05,280
Ms. Nermin.

839
01:12:08,400 --> 01:12:10,680
Did you know your husband would come?

840
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:14,040
God give me patience.

841
01:12:17,720 --> 01:12:19,680
I’ve already lost my mind.

842
01:12:20,560 --> 01:12:22,400
I can’t deal with your nonsense too.

843
01:12:25,080 --> 01:12:26,840
Then how did he get inside?

844
01:12:29,520 --> 01:12:30,720
How did he escape?

845
01:12:31,160 --> 01:12:32,240
Why didn’t you stop him?

846
01:12:32,320 --> 01:12:33,360
Ms. Müzeyyen, please.

847
01:12:33,680 --> 01:12:35,720
Who do you think you are, talking
back to me?

848
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:41,200
Enough.

849
01:12:43,040 --> 01:12:44,560
Please, this is not the time.

850
01:12:46,280 --> 01:12:48,160
Ateş might be in danger outside.

851
01:12:48,720 --> 01:12:50,519
But you are here...

852
01:12:50,520 --> 01:12:51,520
Mom, come on.

853
01:13:08,000 --> 01:13:09,000
Mercan.

854
01:13:09,920 --> 01:13:10,920
Wait, please.

855
01:13:11,720 --> 01:13:13,720
My brother Ateş
will hold me accountable for this.

856
01:13:14,440 --> 01:13:18,360
Besides, if something bad
had happened, wouldn’t we hear something?

857
01:13:32,560 --> 01:13:34,639
Even if he hides in the deepest hole...

858
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:36,160
you will find him.

859
01:13:41,600 --> 01:13:43,560
Not even
a bird will fly around the mansion.

860
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:46,200
Two people...

861
01:13:46,201 --> 01:13:48,720
will stand guard at the gate all night.

862
01:14:02,400 --> 01:14:04,080
Onur, Gencay, you watch the gate.

863
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:05,800
You two come with me.

864
01:14:36,400 --> 01:14:37,760
Thank God you’re okay.

865
01:14:45,160 --> 01:14:46,800
Thank God you’re here.

866
01:14:47,360 --> 01:14:48,520
Thank God you’re alright.

867
01:14:59,920 --> 01:15:00,920
Ateş.

868
01:15:04,840 --> 01:15:06,680
Ateş,
how did that man get into this mansion?

869
01:15:07,080 --> 01:15:08,680
What are the guards outside doing?

870
01:15:15,400 --> 01:15:17,480
He knows
the mansion and its surroundings very well.

871
01:15:20,440 --> 01:15:22,720
He must have entered from nearby.

872
01:15:27,120 --> 01:15:28,640
We’ll find out tomorrow how he got in.

873
01:15:29,000 --> 01:15:30,000
Don’t worry.

874
01:15:30,040 --> 01:15:31,480
How can we not worry?

875
01:15:32,160 --> 01:15:34,000
The man is
a killer with blood on his hands.

876
01:15:34,320 --> 01:15:35,800
He clearly came to kill.

877
01:15:39,600 --> 01:15:40,760
I’m going to my room.

878
01:15:55,640 --> 01:15:56,960
Mercan, are you okay?

879
01:15:58,320 --> 01:15:59,320
I’m fine.

880
01:15:59,760 --> 01:16:00,800
I’m fine, nothing’s wrong.

881
01:16:01,160 --> 01:16:02,160
Come.

882
01:16:02,400 --> 01:16:03,400
Ateş.

883
01:16:15,120 --> 01:16:16,320
I’d better go to my room too.

884
01:16:17,520 --> 01:16:18,520
Good night.

885
01:16:23,480 --> 01:16:24,680
How are you?

886
01:16:26,520 --> 01:16:27,800
I was worried about you too.

887
01:16:28,680 --> 01:16:31,440
Just frustration, nothing more.

888
01:16:32,640 --> 01:16:34,280
They never let things settle.

889
01:16:36,480 --> 01:16:37,480
I should go.

890
01:16:46,800 --> 01:16:48,880
I can’t allow that, Demet.

891
01:16:50,080 --> 01:16:51,080
Why?

892
01:16:51,280 --> 01:16:53,136
Not while your brother
and Haydar are out there.

893
01:16:53,160 --> 01:16:54,160
It’s not safe.

894
01:16:54,680 --> 01:16:56,800
I feel terrible, Cemal.

895
01:16:57,960 --> 01:16:59,600
I can’t even bear what my brother did...

896
01:17:00,600 --> 01:17:03,640
I don’t know how Ateş and Mercan endure it.

897
01:17:05,640 --> 01:17:08,840
I feel ashamed every time I look at them.

898
01:17:10,680 --> 01:17:14,319
If I go, I might find something about where
he is.

899
01:17:14,320 --> 01:17:16,320
This is not up for discussion, Demet.

900
01:17:17,680 --> 01:17:19,240
It wouldn’t be safe for you to go out.

901
01:17:21,040 --> 01:17:23,280
I’m afraid
your brother might even harm you.

902
01:18:17,000 --> 01:18:18,000
Slowly.

903
01:18:37,480 --> 01:18:39,680
You’re okay, right? Tell me the truth.

904
01:18:40,480 --> 01:18:42,040
If you want, we can go to the hospital.

905
01:18:42,400 --> 01:18:43,400
No need.

906
01:18:44,160 --> 01:18:45,160
I’m fine.

907
01:18:48,400 --> 01:18:50,200
When I saw you with your father,
I panicked.

908
01:18:51,480 --> 01:18:54,200
I thought he would hurt you.

909
01:18:55,440 --> 01:18:57,800
I was afraid something would happen to you
too.

910
01:19:02,040 --> 01:19:04,120
Why
didn’t you shout when you saw your father?

911
01:19:04,640 --> 01:19:05,800
Why didn’t you ask for help?

912
01:19:06,680 --> 01:19:10,600
I thought if I talked, he might calm down.

913
01:19:11,560 --> 01:19:12,800
But he had lost his mind.

914
01:19:15,960 --> 01:19:17,040
Please don’t do that again.

915
01:19:18,200 --> 01:19:19,600
Do you hear me? Don’t do that.

916
01:19:20,280 --> 01:19:22,040
What if something had happened to you?

917
01:19:22,280 --> 01:19:23,960
What if he had shot you?

918
01:19:28,280 --> 01:19:30,240
If he wanted to hurt me, he would have.

919
01:19:31,720 --> 01:19:32,880
But he didn’t.

920
01:19:35,360 --> 01:19:37,360
He only thinks I betrayed him.

921
01:19:41,880 --> 01:19:42,880
It’s over now.

922
01:19:44,200 --> 01:19:45,200
It’s all over.

923
01:19:45,960 --> 01:19:46,960
Try to forget.

924
01:19:48,520 --> 01:19:50,520
Even if we forget, they don’t.

925
01:19:51,960 --> 01:19:55,160
Neither his anger nor Ms. Müzeyyen’s will
fade.

926
01:19:56,040 --> 01:19:58,280
Why
are they doing this, why won’t they stop?

927
01:20:04,920 --> 01:20:05,560
You...

928
01:20:05,840 --> 01:20:07,800
He kept saying he would kill you.

929
01:20:09,960 --> 01:20:12,480
My biggest fear
in this life is something happening to you.

930
01:20:16,920 --> 01:20:21,480
Sometimes I want to hide you from everyone
and everything.

931
01:20:26,400 --> 01:20:30,000
The
way he looked today, the things he said...

932
01:20:32,280 --> 01:20:34,440
It
Didn’t feel like my father standing there.

933
01:20:35,880 --> 01:20:37,640
It felt like a stranger.

934
01:20:41,160 --> 01:20:42,559
But...

935
01:20:42,560 --> 01:20:44,280
But he is my father.

936
01:20:48,840 --> 01:20:50,400
I wish it weren’t like this.

937
01:20:58,800 --> 01:20:59,800
Don’t cry.

938
01:21:01,040 --> 01:21:02,480
I can’t bear it, you know that.

939
01:21:27,480 --> 01:21:30,800
Didn’t I
tell you not to do anything behind my back?

940
01:21:31,720 --> 01:21:33,440
Why are you going behind my back?

941
01:21:34,080 --> 01:21:37,160
I wanted to get rid
of that man. Look at the state I’m in now.

942
01:21:39,160 --> 01:21:41,920
I’m tired of living like this. I
want to go back home.

943
01:21:45,360 --> 01:21:48,040
Should I bring you whatever food
you want too?

944
01:21:49,200 --> 01:21:50,200
Tea, coffee?

945
01:21:50,840 --> 01:21:51,960
Don’t mock me, Nezir.

946
01:21:52,200 --> 01:21:53,800
I will mock you, Haydar!

947
01:21:57,120 --> 01:21:58,120
Look at me.

948
01:21:58,880 --> 01:22:00,080
You’re a fugitive now.

949
01:22:01,080 --> 01:22:02,080
Fine.

950
01:22:02,560 --> 01:22:04,400
Forget it. Got it?

951
01:22:05,040 --> 01:22:06,040
No going back home.

952
01:22:07,960 --> 01:22:10,279
From now on,
you’re just a piece in my game.

953
01:22:10,280 --> 01:22:12,480
You have no other way.

954
01:22:13,960 --> 01:22:16,640
Get a grip, Nezir. I’m not your toy.

955
01:22:17,200 --> 01:22:18,920
Fine, you helped me escape, I owe you.

956
01:22:19,840 --> 01:22:20,840
That’s all.

957
01:22:21,400 --> 01:22:22,720
I’ll clear my name and walk free.

958
01:22:25,040 --> 01:22:26,360
And you...

959
01:22:27,440 --> 01:22:30,520
Stay away from Ateş.

960
01:22:31,600 --> 01:22:32,600
He’s mine.

961
01:22:36,160 --> 01:22:37,160
Fine.

962
01:22:38,040 --> 01:22:39,160
I’ll be the one to kill him.

963
01:23:01,080 --> 01:23:02,520
What are you doing?

964
01:23:19,920 --> 01:23:21,520
You’ve completely lost your mind.

965
01:23:29,960 --> 01:23:31,280
You see?

966
01:23:32,920 --> 01:23:34,400
Right in the middle of your forehead.

967
01:23:43,880 --> 01:23:45,200
Did it scare you?

968
01:24:37,960 --> 01:24:39,320
What happened?

969
01:24:42,160 --> 01:24:46,400
I must have hurt myself when I fell.

970
01:24:47,600 --> 01:24:52,120
It’s nothing serious. Just a bruise.

971
01:24:55,160 --> 01:24:59,720
I want to take you away from here,
somewhere you’ll be only with me.

972
01:25:05,520 --> 01:25:06,520
I’ll pick it up.

973
01:25:19,520 --> 01:25:20,920
Your neck is red.

974
01:25:23,240 --> 01:25:24,520
This isn’t from a fall, Mercan.

975
01:25:25,360 --> 01:25:26,520
Did that man hurt you?

976
01:25:27,840 --> 01:25:31,560
It must have happened during the
scuffle while I was trying to grab the gun.

977
01:25:33,200 --> 01:25:35,360
I will make him pay for this.

978
01:25:36,040 --> 01:25:40,240
I swear, one way or another, I will
make him pay for this.

979
01:25:40,560 --> 01:25:41,640
Please calm down.

980
01:25:42,440 --> 01:25:45,640
No matter how
angry he gets, my father wouldn’t hurt me.

981
01:25:46,160 --> 01:25:49,040
That man would throw anyone into
the fire for his own interests, Mercan.

982
01:25:58,120 --> 01:25:59,120
Does it hurt much?

983
01:25:59,440 --> 01:26:03,120
No, I wouldn’t have even noticed
if you hadn’t said it.

984
01:26:03,400 --> 01:26:04,880
I’m telling the truth, believe me.

985
01:26:05,800 --> 01:26:06,800
Wait.

986
01:26:06,920 --> 01:26:07,920
Come here.

987
01:26:19,480 --> 01:26:21,480
Turn around.

988
01:26:38,560 --> 01:26:39,960
You are my most beautiful prayer.

989
01:26:44,520 --> 01:26:49,040
My life began the day
I found a place in your prayers.

990
01:27:16,640 --> 01:27:17,640
Did you take care of it?

991
01:27:21,560 --> 01:27:22,560
Good.

992
01:27:23,120 --> 01:27:24,560
Look, I don’t want anything missing.

993
01:27:26,000 --> 01:27:28,160
Be careful, make sure nothing goes wrong.

994
01:27:35,200 --> 01:27:36,880
Isn’t it a beautiful day, Haydar?

995
01:27:39,400 --> 01:27:40,920
I see you’re in high spirits.

996
01:27:42,160 --> 01:27:43,160
Why shouldn’t I be?

997
01:27:44,120 --> 01:27:45,680
I’ve got a lot of money, Haydar, a lot.

998
01:27:48,720 --> 01:27:52,760
Money saves a man from
all kinds of trouble.

999
01:27:55,640 --> 01:27:56,960
Feels like an explosive day.

1000
01:28:04,760 --> 01:28:06,160
Shall we set off the bombs?

1001
01:28:15,440 --> 01:28:17,840
I sent a very nice gift to Ateş.

1002
01:28:22,800 --> 01:28:24,840
Let’s see if he’ll like it.

1003
01:29:07,760 --> 01:29:11,680
I thought
of an olive sapling as a wedding keepsake.

1004
01:29:12,080 --> 01:29:14,160
We’ll stop by before heading to the office
and talk.

1005
01:29:24,760 --> 01:29:25,800
Ateş!

1006
01:29:30,560 --> 01:29:31,560
Let go!

1007
01:29:35,960 --> 01:29:38,200
What happened? Are you tired, Mr. Ateş?

1008
01:29:52,720 --> 01:29:53,720
What is it?

1009
01:29:56,000 --> 01:30:00,000
Nothing. I just felt like it.

1010
01:30:02,800 --> 01:30:05,120
You
can’t even say you’re tired and resting.

1011
01:30:06,560 --> 01:30:10,080
Who’s tired? If
you want, we can race to the lake.

1012
01:30:12,200 --> 01:30:13,520
Loser does fifty push-ups.

1013
01:30:14,160 --> 01:30:18,880
No crying
when you lose, mind you. As many as I say.

1014
01:30:19,960 --> 01:30:21,960
I admire your confidence.

1015
01:30:22,600 --> 01:30:24,880
But you will lose, fair warning.

1016
01:30:26,960 --> 01:30:29,360
By the way, you’ve got the potential for a
hundred push-ups.

1017
01:30:30,520 --> 01:30:33,080
Let your legs do the talking, not
your mouth.

1018
01:30:34,040 --> 01:30:36,560
I’m giving you a 20-second head
start. Don’t forget this favor.

1019
01:30:37,560 --> 01:30:38,640
What if it were 30?

1020
01:30:39,200 --> 01:30:42,840
Now it’s 15. Go on.

1021
01:30:50,320 --> 01:30:52,240
Last 5 seconds, run!

1022
01:30:56,560 --> 01:30:57,560
15.

1023
01:30:59,520 --> 01:31:00,520
16.

1024
01:31:02,480 --> 01:31:03,480
17.

1025
01:31:04,360 --> 01:31:08,400
What, tired already?
Come on, build some strength in those arms.

1026
01:31:10,920 --> 01:31:11,920
What if it were 20?

1027
01:31:12,880 --> 01:31:16,440
You said 50, you even
said 100 at one point.

1028
01:31:18,360 --> 01:31:19,360
Heartless.

1029
01:31:22,560 --> 01:31:24,856
I can’t bear to
see you like this, alright, that’s enough.

1030
01:31:24,880 --> 01:31:27,120
No, I said 50, it will be 50.

1031
01:31:28,160 --> 01:31:29,920
Get up, come on, get up.

1032
01:31:33,240 --> 01:31:34,520
Listen to your husband for once.

1033
01:31:35,040 --> 01:31:36,040
Alright, my dear husband.

1034
01:31:48,800 --> 01:31:51,560
Mom, calm down now.

1035
01:31:51,920 --> 01:31:56,000
I can’t.
My son’s killer is out there, walking free.

1036
01:31:59,000 --> 01:32:00,720
You’ll see, the police will catch him.

1037
01:32:01,080 --> 01:32:03,520
He has no money anyway, how long
can he run?

1038
01:32:04,600 --> 01:32:09,880
Let him not run. He shouldn’t,
so he can taste death at my hands.

1039
01:32:11,120 --> 01:32:12,520
He’s not worth dirtying your hands.

1040
01:32:18,480 --> 01:32:19,800
Are you alright, Aslı?

1041
01:32:21,160 --> 01:32:24,840
The man lost everything. He’s wandering the
streets.

1042
01:32:28,920 --> 01:32:30,360
Do you really think so?

1043
01:32:31,280 --> 01:32:34,600
Yes, holding onto
deep grudges brought me nothing.

1044
01:32:37,000 --> 01:32:39,400
Once a person realizes what they’ve lost,
they feel lighter.

1045
01:32:40,360 --> 01:32:43,800
No, I don’t accept that.

1046
01:32:46,480 --> 01:32:47,520
I haven’t lost yet.

1047
01:32:48,480 --> 01:32:50,120
What are you planning?

1048
01:32:51,720 --> 01:32:53,960
I
Won’t have peace until they all drop dead.

1049
01:32:55,360 --> 01:32:56,360
No.

1050
01:33:13,120 --> 01:33:14,120
Yes?

1051
01:33:26,040 --> 01:33:28,640
Honey, what’s wrong? Zehra?

1052
01:33:29,480 --> 01:33:30,840
Is your stomach upset again?

1053
01:33:31,000 --> 01:33:32,840
Berat, why
are you coming in without knocking?

1054
01:33:37,120 --> 01:33:38,880
Honey, why should I knock?

1055
01:33:39,400 --> 01:33:40,520
Aren’t I your husband?

1056
01:33:42,280 --> 01:33:44,600
Alright, you are.

1057
01:33:44,800 --> 01:33:47,400
Still,
it’s not right to come in without knocking.

1058
01:33:58,800 --> 01:34:00,360
Honey, may I come in?

1059
01:34:02,240 --> 01:34:03,240
Come in.

1060
01:34:08,040 --> 01:34:12,040
Oh, my dear wife.

1061
01:34:12,560 --> 01:34:16,640
My dear, when you
smile, it’s like roses bloom on your face.

1062
01:34:17,600 --> 01:34:18,640
My beauty.

1063
01:34:19,240 --> 01:34:20,880
Your hair looks so lovely.

1064
01:34:21,200 --> 01:34:22,200
Thank you.

1065
01:34:23,120 --> 01:34:24,120
You’re welcome.

1066
01:34:26,440 --> 01:34:28,920
Here’s the list of things to get.

1067
01:34:29,360 --> 01:34:30,360
Where?

1068
01:34:30,680 --> 01:34:31,680
Here.

1069
01:34:32,120 --> 01:34:34,280
My mother wanted
you to handle it as soon as possible.

1070
01:34:34,400 --> 01:34:35,400
We will, eventually.

1071
01:34:35,880 --> 01:34:39,800
No, Berat. She said it’s
urgent, your mother will get upset.

1072
01:34:42,400 --> 01:34:43,680
Is that so?

1073
01:34:44,400 --> 01:34:44,840
Then I’m going.

1074
01:34:44,920 --> 01:34:45,920
Go on then.

1075
01:34:49,080 --> 01:34:49,720
I’m going.

1076
01:34:50,080 --> 01:34:51,080
Go.

1077
01:34:51,600 --> 01:34:52,600
Easy work.

1078
01:34:52,800 --> 01:34:53,920
Same to you, bye bye.

1079
01:35:31,600 --> 01:35:32,600
Finally.

1080
01:35:39,360 --> 01:35:40,560
Good morning, Ms. Müzeyyen.

1081
01:35:41,040 --> 01:35:43,240
It’s not
proper to keep people waiting at the door.

1082
01:35:43,800 --> 01:35:46,040
You’ve turned this place into a revolving
door.

1083
01:35:47,880 --> 01:35:49,320
Get to the point, I have work to do.

1084
01:35:50,360 --> 01:35:51,760
Of course, I’ll get to the point.

1085
01:35:51,960 --> 01:35:52,960
Would I ever upset you?

1086
01:35:53,440 --> 01:35:54,960
I put the house up for sale.

1087
01:35:55,760 --> 01:35:57,840
I’m thinking of buying a nice place.

1088
01:35:58,600 --> 01:36:01,000
Airy, with a fine view.

1089
01:36:01,760 --> 01:36:02,760
What’s that to me?

1090
01:36:03,800 --> 01:36:07,280
What’s it
to you? I’ll be taking the loan from you.

1091
01:36:09,520 --> 01:36:11,360
We can’t fit in that house anymore.

1092
01:36:12,560 --> 01:36:14,480
Have you lost your mind, Saliha?

1093
01:36:15,320 --> 01:36:18,320
No. I’m perfectly sound.

1094
01:36:19,560 --> 01:36:20,640
Look, Ms. Müzeyyen.

1095
01:36:21,280 --> 01:36:24,560
I’ve put up with you
for years, but enough is enough.

1096
01:36:25,640 --> 01:36:28,800
If you give me my money, there won’t be any
trouble.

1097
01:36:38,640 --> 01:36:43,240
And don’t keep me waiting here again.

1098
01:36:44,960 --> 01:36:45,960
We’ll fall out, I swear.

1099
01:36:56,440 --> 01:36:57,440
Insolent.

1100
01:36:59,880 --> 01:37:01,680
Sour-faced thing.

1101
01:37:14,960 --> 01:37:16,560
Ateş! Ateş!

1102
01:37:20,000 --> 01:37:21,560
I’m coming too.

1103
01:37:22,400 --> 01:37:24,880
No need.
I’ll go to the office and come right back.

1104
01:37:25,200 --> 01:37:26,360
I won’t be late, don’t worry.

1105
01:37:28,000 --> 01:37:31,360
After your father’s threats, are you really
going alone?

1106
01:37:34,040 --> 01:37:35,040
Absolutely not.

1107
01:37:36,000 --> 01:37:37,560
I don’t want to worry about you.

1108
01:37:39,480 --> 01:37:40,480
Then stop worrying.

1109
01:37:42,120 --> 01:37:44,600
I won’t let this limit my life.

1110
01:37:44,800 --> 01:37:45,960
Don’t worry, I won’t be late.

1111
01:37:47,360 --> 01:37:48,360
My love.

1112
01:37:48,640 --> 01:37:51,640
Look,
you’re right, you’re speaking the truth.

1113
01:37:53,080 --> 01:37:56,160
But
after last night, I can’t leave you alone.

1114
01:37:56,320 --> 01:37:57,320
I’m coming too.

1115
01:38:00,960 --> 01:38:02,520
You’re going to protect me, is that it?

1116
01:38:03,520 --> 01:38:04,520
Yes.

1117
01:38:05,120 --> 01:38:06,640
I’ve done it before, I’ll do it again.

1118
01:38:07,840 --> 01:38:08,840
You will, I know.

1119
01:38:12,000 --> 01:38:13,680
Saying no won’t make a difference, right?

1120
01:38:16,160 --> 01:38:17,240
You’ll do as you’re told.

1121
01:38:18,640 --> 01:38:20,320
Come on, when have I ever not listened?

1122
01:38:23,520 --> 01:38:25,200
Alright, alright, I’ll listen.

1123
01:38:27,600 --> 01:38:29,720
Get in, come on, you troublemaker.

1124
01:38:37,400 --> 01:38:39,120
Here we go again with the commands.

1125
01:38:39,920 --> 01:38:41,480
Stop complaining, get in.

1126
01:39:19,480 --> 01:39:20,480
Anywhere is fine.

1127
01:39:20,800 --> 01:39:21,800
Thanks, man.

1128
01:39:23,720 --> 01:39:25,200
You did that on purpose, didn’t you?

1129
01:39:26,600 --> 01:39:29,400
You dragged us into stores we weren’t even
going to shop at.

1130
01:39:31,480 --> 01:39:33,960
Since we were out,
we took care of everything. Not bad, right?

1131
01:39:34,600 --> 01:39:37,120
We need to
go to the company. They’re waiting for us.

1132
01:39:38,240 --> 01:39:41,280
I’m exhausted. How
about we catch our breath first?

1133
01:39:49,560 --> 01:39:52,000
I’m telling you, I love you, girl.

1134
01:39:53,480 --> 01:39:56,320
I won’t let anyone else have you. Got it?

1135
01:39:56,760 --> 01:40:00,360
I told you I have nothing to do with you.
Don’t you understand? Please leave me alone.

1136
01:40:02,120 --> 01:40:05,000
If you’re not mine, I’ll kill you.

1137
01:40:06,440 --> 01:40:08,440
Girl,
the boy loves you so much, can’t you see?

1138
01:40:25,040 --> 01:40:26,040
Ateş.

1139
01:40:26,840 --> 01:40:28,000
The woman is asking for help.

1140
01:40:28,400 --> 01:40:28,760
What?

1141
01:40:29,360 --> 01:40:30,920
She’s asking for help.

1142
01:40:39,800 --> 01:40:43,680
Hey. Leave the woman alone. Get out of here
before I call the police.

1143
01:40:43,920 --> 01:40:44,920
Mercan.

1144
01:40:46,760 --> 01:40:48,120
Are you talking to us?

1145
01:40:48,760 --> 01:40:49,800
Yes, I’m talking to you.

1146
01:40:50,560 --> 01:40:50,800
Mercan.

1147
01:40:51,360 --> 01:40:53,720
Look after the woman next to you, man.

1148
01:40:57,200 --> 01:40:58,200
Watch your mouth.

1149
01:40:58,760 --> 01:41:01,560
I’ll talk however I want. Shut that woman
up.

1150
01:41:02,600 --> 01:41:05,360
If you can’t, I will.

1151
01:41:05,520 --> 01:41:06,520
What did you just say?

1152
01:41:14,240 --> 01:41:15,560
Bro, okay.

1153
01:41:15,760 --> 01:41:16,760
Break it up.

1154
01:41:20,840 --> 01:41:23,360
Bro, okay.

1155
01:41:29,120 --> 01:41:30,120
Let go!

1156
01:41:30,800 --> 01:41:32,640
Help, guys!

1157
01:41:38,600 --> 01:41:39,879
Separate them!

1158
01:41:39,880 --> 01:41:41,480
Come here.

1159
01:41:54,720 --> 01:42:00,200
What’s this, girl?

1160
01:42:01,960 --> 01:42:03,440
It came for Mr. Ateş.

1161
01:42:04,800 --> 01:42:05,920
Well, well. What is it?

1162
01:42:06,600 --> 01:42:09,800
I don’t know. Probably a wedding gift.

1163
01:42:11,040 --> 01:42:13,240
Good. Put
it in his room so it doesn’t get forgotten.

1164
01:42:13,760 --> 01:42:15,320
Okay, mom.

1165
01:43:23,360 --> 01:43:26,040
I’m planning a vacation after the wedding.

1166
01:43:30,920 --> 01:43:33,680
After everything, I need some rest.

1167
01:43:35,560 --> 01:43:36,560
Where will you go?

1168
01:43:38,920 --> 01:43:40,080
Maybe Italy.

1169
01:43:41,120 --> 01:43:43,320
I’ll also deal with the project there.

1170
01:43:43,640 --> 01:43:45,240
Sure, of course. Go ahead.

1171
01:43:46,520 --> 01:43:48,280
After all,
there’s nothing keeping you here.

1172
01:43:49,320 --> 01:43:51,240
You’re right. We’ve been through a lot.

1173
01:43:54,240 --> 01:43:57,960
Yes. A lot has happened.

1174
01:44:00,080 --> 01:44:01,960
I can’t get over what my brother did.

1175
01:44:05,040 --> 01:44:08,680
I don’t understand how
he could leave me alone.

1176
01:44:11,560 --> 01:44:14,680
I
Feel completely alone in this whole world.

1177
01:44:17,880 --> 01:44:18,880
You’re not, Demet.

1178
01:44:20,120 --> 01:44:21,120
I…

1179
01:44:26,520 --> 01:44:27,520
Yes?

1180
01:44:29,800 --> 01:44:32,440
What do you
mean? You’re not supposed to leave either!

1181
01:44:35,560 --> 01:44:37,560
Okay, hang up. I’ll handle it.

1182
01:44:38,280 --> 01:44:38,760
What happened?

1183
01:44:39,120 --> 01:44:40,840
Ateş and Mercan. They’re at the station.

1184
01:44:41,120 --> 01:44:42,120
They got into a fight.

1185
01:44:42,520 --> 01:44:43,520
Oh come on!

1186
01:45:09,960 --> 01:45:13,440
Trouble never leaves you, I’m telling you.

1187
01:45:13,960 --> 01:45:15,960
We’ll be seeing you here more often.

1188
01:45:28,320 --> 01:45:30,800
What happened? Are
you cold? You’re not used to this, are you?

1189
01:45:35,360 --> 01:45:37,400
Thanks to you, we didn’t end up in a cell.

1190
01:45:39,600 --> 01:45:42,320
The woman asked for help. I helped.

1191
01:45:43,080 --> 01:45:45,440
What help? I didn’t see anything.

1192
01:45:46,920 --> 01:45:50,160
She did this. It means “I need help.”

1193
01:45:52,760 --> 01:45:53,920
Did she really do that?

1194
01:45:54,400 --> 01:45:58,599
Yes. If only the woman would show up…

1195
01:45:58,600 --> 01:46:02,080
She must’ve run away out of fear in all that
chaos. Poor thing. What else could she do?

1196
01:46:04,960 --> 01:46:06,320
The police will find her anyway.

1197
01:46:08,280 --> 01:46:10,320
I
Already told the police she asked for help.

1198
01:46:11,160 --> 01:46:12,960
I think those guys are done for now.

1199
01:46:14,760 --> 01:46:16,880
Done, done. I think so too.

1200
01:46:17,400 --> 01:46:19,000
You broke one of their arms.

1201
01:46:21,280 --> 01:46:24,680
What was
I supposed to do? The guy tried to hit you.

1202
01:46:25,120 --> 01:46:27,480
And you busted his lip too.

1203
01:46:29,560 --> 01:46:31,480
If anyone tries to mess with you…

1204
01:46:32,400 --> 01:46:34,040
…that’s what they’ll get.

1205
01:46:41,680 --> 01:46:44,320
We were supposed
to be home, and look at where we ended up.

1206
01:46:45,600 --> 01:46:46,840
We got blamed for nothing.

1207
01:46:48,000 --> 01:46:50,080
Let
the woman speak. We’ll see who’s guilty.

1208
01:46:56,480 --> 01:46:58,640
Why did you even get involved anyway?

1209
01:47:01,440 --> 01:47:04,080
You should’ve left
it to me, I would’ve beaten them cleanly.

1210
01:47:04,160 --> 01:47:07,200
Wouldn’t that be
better? They tried to attack you.

1211
01:47:07,280 --> 01:47:09,560
What was I supposed to do? Stand there and
watch?

1212
01:47:10,160 --> 01:47:12,239
The fight started because you mouthed off.

1213
01:47:12,240 --> 01:47:15,040
I’m telling you, the woman asked for help.
I saw it.

1214
01:47:57,680 --> 01:47:58,680
What’s wrong, Haydar?

1215
01:48:03,560 --> 01:48:04,760
You don’t look well.

1216
01:48:08,760 --> 01:48:09,840
You keep fidgeting nonstop.

1217
01:48:10,960 --> 01:48:12,360
Why did you tie me up?

1218
01:48:13,320 --> 01:48:14,920
Why are you doing this? Are you crazy?

1219
01:48:20,920 --> 01:48:23,400
I am crazy, I’m sick, alright?

1220
01:48:23,760 --> 01:48:25,720
I’m obsessed with Mercan.

1221
01:48:28,480 --> 01:48:29,920
Why do you think I kidnapped you?

1222
01:48:30,800 --> 01:48:32,800
For your pretty eyes?

1223
01:48:33,200 --> 01:48:36,360
You’re very valuable to me right now.

1224
01:48:37,320 --> 01:48:38,920
You’re the key to everything I have.

1225
01:48:53,120 --> 01:48:54,120
Alright.

1226
01:49:10,480 --> 01:49:12,280
Let’s see if Ateş likes his surprise.

1227
01:49:31,200 --> 01:49:32,920
Ateş…

1228
01:49:36,560 --> 01:49:38,120
Do you think we’ll get out of here?

1229
01:49:42,160 --> 01:49:43,160
I guess we will.

1230
01:49:45,000 --> 01:49:46,000
You guess?

1231
01:49:47,640 --> 01:49:49,720
Why are you so relaxed?

1232
01:49:50,560 --> 01:49:52,240
What do you expect me to do?

1233
01:49:53,120 --> 01:49:55,240
You should’ve thought
of that before beating them up.

1234
01:49:56,400 --> 01:49:59,360
If what you said is true,
it worked out though.

1235
01:49:59,480 --> 01:50:04,920
Of course it did. They
even got off easy. We really beat them…

1236
01:50:08,520 --> 01:50:09,520
Calm down.

1237
01:50:14,920 --> 01:50:16,120
Fiery princess.

1238
01:50:17,840 --> 01:50:18,840
Alright.

1239
01:50:19,640 --> 01:50:24,160
Okay, I’m calm. What if they can’t find the
woman?

1240
01:50:25,680 --> 01:50:27,280
What if those men hurt her?

1241
01:50:28,960 --> 01:50:30,400
Nothing will happen, don’t worry.

1242
01:50:32,240 --> 01:50:34,640
If what you said
is true, I won’t let them get away with it.

1243
01:50:34,920 --> 01:50:38,720
But you keep saying “if what you
said is true.” I told you I saw it.

1244
01:50:39,240 --> 01:50:42,800
Alright, you’re right. If you say you saw
it, you did.

1245
01:50:43,760 --> 01:50:49,160
Then we’ll get out soon, right?

1246
01:50:53,960 --> 01:50:57,480
Hard to say. Maybe we won’t.

1247
01:51:00,000 --> 01:51:01,000
No.

1248
01:51:01,280 --> 01:51:02,680
No, you’re doing this on purpose.

1249
01:51:07,320 --> 01:51:09,440
You’re doing this so I won’t beat anyone
up again.

1250
01:51:10,440 --> 01:51:14,519
I think you
shouldn’t. If you acted like a proper lady…

1251
01:51:14,520 --> 01:51:17,640
Wouldn’t it
be better if I handled the beating cleanly?

1252
01:51:17,840 --> 01:51:22,200
No, sir. We’re not useless either.

1253
01:51:28,200 --> 01:51:29,880
How much longer will we stay here?

1254
01:51:32,280 --> 01:51:33,720
We really messed those guys up.

1255
01:51:39,720 --> 01:51:41,319
If they don’t withdraw their complaint…

1256
01:51:41,320 --> 01:51:43,080
…they’ll send us to court from here.

1257
01:51:43,760 --> 01:51:48,240
Then to prison. You already learned how to
pace around.

1258
01:51:48,520 --> 01:51:50,400
You’ll learn to play the saz inside too.

1259
01:51:53,800 --> 01:51:57,640
Seriously?
Are we going to prison for beating someone?

1260
01:51:58,840 --> 01:51:59,840
What about the wedding?

1261
01:52:01,880 --> 01:52:02,880
The wedding?

1262
01:52:06,520 --> 01:52:10,040
You know
what we’ll do? We’ll call the registrar in.

1263
01:52:10,120 --> 01:52:11,719
We’ll have a prison wedding there.

1264
01:52:11,720 --> 01:52:15,240
You’re making fun of me.

1265
01:52:16,080 --> 01:52:17,799
A little.

1266
01:52:17,800 --> 01:52:19,280
Come on, Ateş.

1267
01:52:20,920 --> 01:52:24,120
Fine, fine.

1268
01:52:39,480 --> 01:52:42,880
Alright, you’re free
to go. We found the woman.

1269
01:52:43,320 --> 01:52:44,840
She confirmed what you said.

1270
01:52:46,240 --> 01:52:47,240
I told you.

1271
01:53:28,200 --> 01:53:31,040
For a
moment, I thought we’d never make it home.

1272
01:53:32,480 --> 01:53:34,520
Yes, another adventure comes to an end.

1273
01:53:34,680 --> 01:53:36,680
I sincerely congratulate everyone involved.

1274
01:53:38,320 --> 01:53:40,200
By the way, I bought you prayer beads.

1275
01:53:40,600 --> 01:53:43,320
You can swing them while
telling your holding cell stories.

1276
01:53:49,720 --> 01:53:51,799
As long as Ms. Mercan doesn’t behave…

1277
01:53:51,800 --> 01:53:56,119
…we’ll have many more
adventures. Good thing she didn’t.

1278
01:53:56,120 --> 01:53:59,200
See, you didn’t believe me.

1279
01:54:02,720 --> 01:54:04,720
But as always, I was right.

1280
01:54:07,040 --> 01:54:08,080
That’s my lioness wife.

1281
01:54:10,360 --> 01:54:12,720
You saved that woman’s life, my lady.

1282
01:54:14,520 --> 01:54:16,120
Mercan was right.

1283
01:54:16,480 --> 01:54:18,960
I didn’t notice. The woman was asking for
help.

1284
01:54:22,280 --> 01:54:25,400
One of those
men was supposedly her coworker.

1285
01:54:26,240 --> 01:54:28,880
He “loved” her. He was harassing her.

1286
01:54:30,320 --> 01:54:34,280
What kind of love
is that? Is there fear where there’s love?

1287
01:54:37,920 --> 01:54:40,040
I
Can’t forget the look in that woman’s eyes.

1288
01:54:41,600 --> 01:54:42,840
Don’t think about it now.

1289
01:54:43,160 --> 01:54:46,760
We’ll handle both the woman and the man.

1290
01:54:47,400 --> 01:54:51,079
Leave that
to me. From now on, that man won’t even…

1291
01:54:51,080 --> 01:54:54,360
…be able to come near her, let alone stay
in the same city. We’ll take care of it.

1292
01:54:55,240 --> 01:54:58,480
Normally I’d ask what you did, but I won’t
now.

1293
01:55:01,520 --> 01:55:04,200
What women go through because of men…

1294
01:55:07,360 --> 01:55:10,640
If only
they understood women want a bit of peace.

1295
01:55:10,840 --> 01:55:14,040
Brother, I’m telling you, let’s not get
into this topic. We won’t get out of it.

1296
01:55:14,760 --> 01:55:15,760
I agree, let’s not.

1297
01:55:17,200 --> 01:55:19,600
Look how well they know what suits them.

1298
01:55:21,080 --> 01:55:23,040
Alright guys, we’re heading inside.

1299
01:55:23,680 --> 01:55:24,800
Come on.

1300
01:55:32,000 --> 01:55:35,560
What was that? A gesture
for asking help? We learned that too.

1301
01:55:35,800 --> 01:55:37,600
She did something like this though?

1302
